(secondQuint)Assessment of Dolutegravir Removed by Hemodialysis in HIV-infected Patients With End-stage Renal Disease.

 The prevalence of chronic renal disease and end-stage renal disease (ESRD) is increasing in the HIV-positive population.

 This means that an increasing number of HIV-infected patients will need renal replacement therapy.

However, little is known about DTG removal from plasma by HD in patients with ESRD.

 Objective: to evaluate the effect of HD on DTG clearance as well as on DTG plasma concentrations at steady state in HIV-infected patients with ESRD undergoing HD.

